# HomePage Initial Prompt

I need you to build a customizable local business directory homepage that integrates with my existing MVP upload system. This will be the public-facing homepage with full admin customization capabilities.

## Tech Stack & Integration
- Next.js 14+ with App Router and TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS for styling
- Supabase database (existing connection via lib/supabase.ts)
- Integration with existing MVP admin system
- SEO optimized with schema markup
- No src directory - use root-level structure

## Database Schema Integration
Use existing `production_businesses` table to extract data. Also create these new tables for admin customization:

```sql
CREATE TABLE site_settings (
  id UUID DEFAULT gen_random_uuid() PRIMARY KEY,
  directory_name TEXT DEFAULT 'Local Business Directory',
  logo_url TEXT,
  primary_color TEXT DEFAULT '#2563eb',
  secondary_color TEXT DEFAULT '#1e40af',
  hero_title TEXT DEFAULT 'Find Local Businesses',
  hero_subtitle TEXT DEFAULT 'Discover Quality Services',
  hero_description TEXT DEFAULT 'Find local businesses across America...',
  browse_all_cta TEXT DEFAULT 'Browse All States',
  view_top_cta TEXT DEFAULT 'View Top States',
  bystate_title TEXT DEFAULT 'Local Businesses by State',
  bystate_description TEXT DEFAULT 'Find businesses in your state...',
  show_bystate_section BOOLEAN DEFAULT true,
  updated_at TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE DEFAULT NOW()
);

-- Insert default settings
INSERT INTO site_settings (id) VALUES ('00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001');
```

## Homepage Components Required

### 1. Navigation Bar
- Logo (from site_settings.logo_url or default)
- Menu items: Home, Browse States, About Us, Contact
- "Browse Directory" button (styled prominently)
- Responsive mobile menu
- Same styling as the reference image

### 2. Hero Section
- Dynamic background gradient (blue like reference)
- Customizable title (site_settings.hero_title)
- Customizable subtitle with highlight color (site_settings.hero_subtitle)
- Description text (site_settings.hero_description)
- 3 Statistics cards with real-time data from database:
  - Total Store Listings (count from production_businesses)
  - States Covered (distinct states from production_businesses)
  - Cities Covered (distinct cities from production_businesses)
- Two CTA buttons (customizable text from site_settings)

### 3. By State Section (Conditional Display)
- Show/hide based on site_settings.show_bystate_section
- Customizable title and description
- Display top 8 states by business count
- State cards with emoji icons:
  - Florida 🌴, Texas ⭐, California 🌴, Pennsylvania 📍
  - Georgia 🍑, Illinois 🏢, Ohio 📍, Missouri 📍
- Each card shows: state name, business count, cities count, "View Directory" link
- Responsive grid layout (2x4 on desktop, 1 column on mobile)

## File Structure to Create/Modify

```
├── app/
│   ├── page.tsx (NEW - Homepage)
│   ├── browse-states/
│   │   └── page.tsx (NEW - Browse States page)
│   ├── about/
│   │   └── page.tsx (NEW - About page)
│   ├── contact/
│   │   └── page.tsx (NEW - Contact page)
│   ├── admin/
│   │   └── settings/
│   │       └── page.tsx (MODIFY - Add homepage settings)
│   └── globals.css (MODIFY - Add custom CSS variables)
├── components/
│   ├── public/
│   │   ├── Navbar.tsx (NEW)
│   │   ├── HeroSection.tsx (NEW)
│   │   ├── StatCard.tsx (NEW)
│   │   ├── ByStateSection.tsx (NEW)
│   │   ├── StateCard.tsx (NEW)
│   │   └── Footer.tsx (NEW)
│   └── admin/
│       └── HomepageSettings.tsx (NEW - Admin customization)
├── hooks/
│   ├── useHomepageData.ts (NEW)
│   └── useSiteSettings.ts (NEW)
├── lib/
│   ├── homepage-utils.ts (NEW)
│   └── seo.ts (NEW - Schema markup)
└── types/
    └── homepage.ts (NEW - TypeScript interfaces)
```

## Key Features Required

### SEO Optimization
- Proper HTML semantic structure
- Schema.org markup for LocalBusinessDirectory
- Meta tags for title, description, og:image
- Structured data for businesses and locations
- Dynamic meta tags based on site settings

### Admin Customization Panel
Add to existing admin settings page:
- Directory name and logo upload
- Color scheme picker (primary/secondary colors)
- Hero section text editing (title, subtitle, description)
- CTA button text customization
- Toggle By State section on/off
- By State section title/description editing
- **Footer customization**:
  - About text editing
  - Contact information (email, phone)
  - Social media links (Facebook, Twitter, LinkedIn)
  - Toggle social media section on/off
- Real-time preview of changes

### Responsive Design
- Mobile-first approach matching reference design
- Gradient backgrounds and card layouts
- Proper touch targets and spacing
- Navigation collapse on mobile

### Database Integration
- Real-time statistics from production_businesses table
- Top states calculation by business count
- City counts per state
- Efficient queries with proper indexing

## TypeScript Interfaces Needed

```typescript
// types/homepage.ts
export interface SiteSettings {
  id: string;
  directory_name: string;
  logo_url?: string;
  primary_color: string;
  secondary_color: string;
  hero_title: string;
  hero_subtitle: string;
  hero_description: string;
  browse_all_cta: string;
  view_top_cta: string;
  bystate_title: string;
  bystate_description: string;
  show_bystate_section: boolean;
  updated_at: string;
}

export interface HomepageStats {
  totalBusinesses: number;
  statesCovered: number;
  citiesCovered: number;
}

export interface StateData {
  state: string;
  businessCount: number;
  cityCount: number;
  emoji: string;
}
```

